00:22:22.470 --> 00:22:24.360 align:middle line:84%
And this is the
story she told me.

00:22:24.360 --> 00:22:27.600 align:middle line:84%
She said that every
morning he'd wake up

00:22:27.600 --> 00:22:30.570 align:middle line:84%
and he'd be overcome
and think, I

00:22:30.570 --> 00:22:32.340 align:middle line:90%
have an idea for a comic strip.

00:22:32.340 --> 00:22:36.033 align:middle line:84%
This is the perfect
idea for a comic.

00:22:36.033 --> 00:22:37.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: This is
before "Peanuts."

00:22:37.450 --> 00:22:38.867 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY:
This is "Peanuts."

00:22:38.867 --> 00:22:41.610 align:middle line:84%
Every morning, his strip,
"Peanuts," he'd think,

00:22:41.610 --> 00:22:43.020 align:middle line:90%
today's the day.

00:22:43.020 --> 00:22:45.800 align:middle line:84%
I've got a perfect
idea for today's strip.

00:22:45.800 --> 00:22:46.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Aha.

00:22:46.600 --> 00:22:47.400 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:22:47.400 --> 00:22:49.710 align:middle line:84%
>>RICHTEL: He'd have an
aha moment like that.

00:22:49.710 --> 00:22:51.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And come
up with his stuff.

00:22:51.210 --> 00:22:52.960 align:middle line:84%
>>RICHTEL: And he'd
start writing all day.

00:22:52.960 --> 00:22:56.040 align:middle line:84%
He'd wake up in the
morning the next day,

00:22:56.040 --> 00:22:59.090 align:middle line:84%
and he would look at his
strip and he'd think,

00:22:59.090 --> 00:23:00.090 align:middle line:90%
I don't think that's it.

00:23:00.090 --> 00:23:04.950 align:middle line:84%
Wait a minute, I have the idea
