It's an interesting time when
you see an explosion of people

00:35:59.920 --> 00:36:03.010 align:middle line:84%
who feel enabled with
all the technology

00:36:03.010 --> 00:36:05.770 align:middle line:90%
to come up with all these ideas.

00:36:05.770 --> 00:36:09.160 align:middle line:84%
But can I key on something your
guest said right there, which

00:36:09.160 --> 00:36:11.260 align:middle line:90%
I think was really important?

00:36:11.260 --> 00:36:15.400 align:middle line:84%
At the very beginning,
he alluded to the fact

00:36:15.400 --> 00:36:19.450 align:middle line:84%
that creativity can be
associated with happiness.

00:36:19.450 --> 00:36:24.660 align:middle line:84%
In one of the pieces of
research I found so compelling

00:36:24.660 --> 00:36:26.130 align:middle line:90%
in this book--

00:36:26.130 --> 00:36:28.500 align:middle line:84%
and, again, I came at
this journalistically,

00:36:28.500 --> 00:36:32.830 align:middle line:84%
not from a position where I
had an ax to grind or something

00:36:32.830 --> 00:36:33.630 align:middle line:90%
to prove.

00:36:33.630 --> 00:36:34.430 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:36:34.430 --> 00:36:39.460 align:middle line:84%
>>RICHTEL: So I was surprised
to see that people who create,

00:36:39.460 --> 00:36:41.460 align:middle line:90%
find themselves happier.

00:36:41.460 --> 00:36:43.050 align:middle line:90%
And the reason--

00:36:43.050 --> 00:36:44.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And wealthier.

00:36:44.670 --> 00:36:46.170 align:middle line:90%
>>RICHTEL: Well, yes, or poorer.

00:36:46.170 --> 00:36:48.415 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] Both.

00:36:48.415 --> 00:36:50.790 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to take a stab
at-- since I can't stump you--

00:36:50.790 --> 00:36:55.170 align:middle line:84%
why creativity is
associated with happiness?

00:36:55.170 --> 00:36:57.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I think it's
an innate personality

00:36:57.930 --> 00:37:00.210 align:middle line:90%
trait of the creative person.

00:37:00.210 --> 00:37:02.377 align:middle line:84%
>>RICHTEL: And you think
once expressed, it allows--

00:37:02.377 --> 00:37:03.177 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:37:03.177 --> 00:37:04.197 align:middle line:90%
>>RICHTEL: Yeah, so--

00:37:04.197 --> 00:37:06.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They're doing
what they like to do.

00:37:06.030 --> 00:37:08.340 align:middle line:84%
>>RICHTEL: That is
absolutely the case.

00:37:08.340 --> 00:37:10.200 align:middle line:10%
There's one other
piece of research

00:37:10.200 --> 00:37:14.490 align:middle line:10%
that really struck me for those
who tend not to be creative

00:37:14.490 --> 00:37:17.570 align:middle line:10%
but want to experience it.

00:37:17.570 --> 00:37:20.600 align:middle line:10%
There's research that
suggests when people create,

00:37:20.600 --> 00:37:25.100 align:middle line:10%
meaning they express ideas
that they haven't expressed

00:37:25.100 --> 00:37:28.970 align:middle line:10%
before that are
honest and authentic,

00:37:28.970 --> 00:37:31.520 align:middle line:10%
that they feel unburdened.

00:37:31.520 --> 00:37:34.280 align:middle line:84%
That some weight has
come off their shoulders.

00:37:34.280 --> 00:37:36.380 align:middle line:84%
And what's interesting
about this research

00:37:36.380 --> 00:37:40.430 align:middle line:84%
is it suggests when
people do a creative act--

00:37:40.430 --> 00:37:46.050 align:middle line:84%
pick up a paintbrush, start
a business, write a song--

00:37:46.050 --> 00:37:50.640 align:middle line:84%
they might feel unburdened
from weights unassociated even

00:37:50.640 --> 00:37:52.800 align:middle line:84%
with the creativity
they're expressing.

00:37:52.800 --> 00:37:56.670 align:middle line:84%
So there is something
very natural

00:37:56.670 --> 00:37:59.790 align:middle line:84%
and vital about that
act of expression.

00:37:59.790 --> 00:38:01.322 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And healthy.

00:38:01.322 --> 00:38:02.530 align:middle line:90%
>>RICHTEL: Extremely healthy.

00:38:02.530 --> 00:38:04.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How do people
track your work?

